Not an ECO line, but not poor for white. Black has to be careful not to get his knights pinned all over.
The white squared black bishop is often a very useful piece in the benoni, and is better than white's white squared bishop, often boxed in by its own pawns.
Nf3 is stronger, white shouldn't make the black squares (specifically e5 and d4) so easy to control.
